709380f-a.text:
6th Avenue, 20th Street, to 19th . East side. (Before Reconstruction).
President Borough of Manhattan.

709378f-a.text:
Sixth Avenue, east side, north from West 19th Street. Appearing progressively are the former Alexander and Cammeyer Buildings, the Protestant Episcopal Church of the Holy Communion, the Masonic Temple building and the Hotel McAlpin. Towering above the church is the dominant Empire State Building. View 2 is the same area photographed immediately following the demolition of the old 6th
Avenue "EL" structure.
June 11, 1933 "
October 28, 1939
P. L. Sperr

But rest picture taken March 2, shows the L is gone

(the EL, or the L = elevated train)
